    • replaceLocusIcons

      void replaceLocusIcons​(@NonNull MultipartMainDto multipartMainDto)
      1. Finds all the <StyleMap>s with "id" references to photo thumbnails 2. If a <StyleMap> with a previously created "id" to the current MultipartMainDto#getPictogramName() exists it: 2.1 Replaces all the <Placemark>s <styleUrl>s with that existing <StyleMap> 3. If no <StyleMap> for that MultipartMainDto#getPictogramName() exists it: 3.1 It gets a first <StyleMap> as an example, clones it and its 'normal' and 'highlight' <Style>s 3.2 Creates a new <StyleMap> and its 'normal' and 'highlight' inner <Style>s based on the clone. 3.3 Replaces all the <Placemark>s <styleUrl>s with that new cloned <StyleMap> 4. Deletes all the <StyleMap>s from the Document with "id" to photo thumbnails. As well as their included "Normal" and "Highlighted" <Style>s 5. Finds all the <Style>s with "id" references to photo thumbnails 6. If <Style> with 'id' as a such a pictogram name as: MultipartMainDto#getPictogramName() exists it: 6.1 Replaces all the <Placemark>s <styleUrl>s to thumbnail with that existing <Style> 7. Deletes all the <Style>s with thumbnail 'id' attributes 8. If no <Style> for that MultipartMainDto#getPictogramName() exists it: 8.1 It gets a first <Style> as an example and clones it 8.2 Creates a new <Style> and new href to icon based on the clone. 8.3 Replaces all the <Placemark>s <styleUrl>s with that new cloned <StyleMap> 9. Deletes all the <Style>s with thumbnail 'id' attributes 10. If MultipartMainDto#getDownloadAs() == DownloadAs.KMZ all the previously deleted photo icons should be excluded from the resultant .zip(.kmz) file.
      Parameters:
      multipartMainDto -

    • replaceStylesInStyleUrls

      private java.util.Map<java.lang.String,​org.w3c.dom.Node> replaceStylesInStyleUrls​(java.lang.String pictogramName)
      All the <styleUrl>s pointers in <Placemark>s with the <Style> (with existing or newly created one) where the 'id' attribute is corresponding to MultipartMainDto#getPictogramName() and <IconHref> is updated as well. Its better to execute this method after replacing StyleMaps in replaceStyleMapsInStyleUrls(String).
      Parameters:
      pictogramName - A replacing filename of the new pictogram.png
      Returns:
      Map<String ('id'),Node(Style)> where <Style>s Nodes can by safely deleted from the Document

    • isLocusPhotoIconThumbnail

      boolean isLocusPhotoIconThumbnail​(org.w3c.dom.Node styleObject)
      In my case full names of the vast majority of icons with photos are like 'file:///sdcard/Locus/cache/images/123456789.png', and the 'Style id='' attribute is the full path above except the extension, 'file:///sdcard/Locus/cache/images/123456789'. 1) isLocusPhotoId(String) So the basic match of 'Style id=""' has to start with 'file:///', contain a Locus-autogenerated part of a full path like '/Locus/cache/images/' and end with a filename with a minimum of 4 signs. 1.1) isLocusPhotoId(String) This app generates a special prefix for 'StyleMap id=styleMapOf:file///[...]'. So the next math has to start with 'styleMapOf:file:///[...]' Also some versions of Locus Map generate icons with only digit names started with a hyphen like "-1245953029.png" and with appropriate 'Style id="-1245953029"', where digits number is from 7 to 10. 2) isLocusPhotoIconHref(String) So the next specific match is better to check only by 'href' where href has to start with any path then a hyphen "-" and then only from 7 to 10 digits and end with ".png" in low or high case. Like "files/-1245953029.png" or "C:/MyFiles/photos/-1245953029.PNG". 2.1) isLocusPhotoIconHref(String) An additional check for 'href' to contain [any_path][any_prefix]locuscacheimages[any_filename_postfix][.png]. It must return true for the photo icon. And the final versions of Locus Map generates just a digital filename for a .png icon from 7 to 10 digits as "1801528832.png". 4) The last specific match also has to be checked by a 'href' full path which has to start with any path ended with '/'and 7 to 10 digits filename with '.png' extension, e.g. "files/12345678.png"
